\c 53
\s1 Mazmur yang ditulis oleh Daud,
\s1 Dengan memakai Mahalat, nyanyian Daud
\q1
\v 1 Orang bodoh berkata di dalam hatinya, “Tidak ada Allah.”
\q1 Mereka menghancurkan; berbuat jahat,
\q2 tidak seorang pun yang melakukan kebaikan.
\b
\q1
\v 2 Allah memandang ke bawah dari surga;
\q1 kepada anak-anak manusia,
\q2 untuk melihat jika ada yang berakal budi dan mencari Allah dengan segenap hatinya.
\q1
\v 3 But they are all morally corrupt;
\q2 no one does what is good/right.
\b
\q1
\v 4 Will all these evil people never learn \add what God will do tothem\add*?
\q1 They act violently toward Yahweh's people while eating the food that he provides,
\q2 and they never pray to Yahweh.
\q1
\v 5 But \add some day\add* those people will become very terrified,
\q2 like they have never been terrified before,
\q1 because God will cause those who are separated from God to die,
\q2 and he will scatter their bones.
\q1 They have rejected God,
\q2 so he will cause them to be \add defeated and\add* completely disgraced.
\b
\q1
\v 6 I wish/desire that someone from Jerusalem [MTY] would come and rescue the Israeli people!
\q2 God, when you bless your people again,
\q1 all the Israeli people, all the descendants of Jacob, will rejoice.